<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-058-229 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 292 267</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Sept 16 1991 v25 n37 p95(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Work management works best. (ways to improve the management ofinformation systems organizations) (Commentary)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shattow, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information systems (IS) organizations required to enhance theefficiency and management of operations may be able to benefitfrom work management systems.andP;  These systems provide an IS-widemethod for managing IS as a real business organization.andP;  Thesystem accomplishes this goal by taking advantage of integratedcontrol applications.andP;  Two important aspects of a well-designedmanagement system include using a single methodology to reinforceplanning, creating standards and controlling reporting.andP;  Workmanagement systems differ from project management softwarepackages because work management systems have a wider scope andcapability.andP;  In contrast, project management packages are not ableto assist with the management of most of the work accomplished inIS environments.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ComparisonMISOffice AutomationProject management systemsInformation systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>